---
import "./styles.b.2.css";
---

<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>User Journey Mapping Specifications</title>
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com" />
    <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin />
    <link
      href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=SpaceGrotesk:wght@400;500;600;700&display=swap"
      rel="stylesheet"
    />
  </head>
  <body>
    <div class="page">
      <header class="hero">
        <div class="hero__meta">
          <div class="pill">UJG • Open Specification</div>
          <div class="pill">Design-time ↔ Runtime</div>
          <div class="pill">Graph-based journeys</div>
        </div>
        <div class="hero__content">
          <h1>User Journey Mapping (UJG)</h1>
          <p>
            A family of open specifications that model user journeys as graphs
            of states and transitions, separating design intent from runtime
            execution to enable validation, measurement, and iteration.
          </p>
          <div class="hero__actions">
            <a class="btn primary" href="/tr/latest/">Latest Technical Report</a
            >
            <a class="btn" href="/ed/">Editor’s Draft Workspace</a>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="hero__stats">
          <div class="stat">
            <span class="stat__value">6</span>
            <span class="stat__label">Core documents</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stat">
            <span class="stat__value">2</span>
            <span class="stat__label">Journey layers</span>
          </div>
          <div class="stat">
            <span class="stat__value">1</span>
            <span class="stat__label">Spec family</span>
          </div>
        </div>
      </header>

      <section class="grid">
        <article class="panel intro">
          <h2>Start here</h2>
          <p>
            UJG is composed of living drafts and stable snapshots. Navigate by
            what you need right now.
          </p>
          <ul class="links">
            <li><a href="/tr/latest/">Latest Technical Report</a></li>
            <li><a href="/ed/">Editor’s Draft workspace</a></li>
            <li><a href="/governance/">Governance</a></li>
            <li><a href="/contributing/">Contributing</a></li>
            <li><a href="https://github.com/">Repository</a></li>
          </ul>
        </article>

        <article class="panel contrast">
          <div class="panel__header">
            <h2>Editor’s Draft (ED)</h2>
            <span class="tag">Always evolving</span>
          </div>
          <p>
            The ED workspace captures the newest ideas, examples, and proposals.
            Documents can change at any time.
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Track upcoming changes while implementing.</li>
            <li>Participate in discussions and contribute.</li>
            <li>Prototype the newest journey patterns.</li>
          </ul>
        </article>

        <article class="panel contrast">
          <div class="panel__header">
            <h2>Technical Reports (TR)</h2>
            <span class="tag">Stable snapshot</span>
          </div>
          <p>
            TRs are versioned releases of stable UJG work, covering the spec
            family as a whole.
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Stable references for citations.</li>
            <li>Consensus-based requirements.</li>
            <li>Reliable baseline for interoperability.</li>
          </ul>
        </article>
      </section>

      <section class="flow">
        <div class="flow__header">
          <h2>What’s inside the UJG family</h2>
          <p>
            Each document focuses on a specific aspect of journey modeling.
            Together, they connect intent, execution, and measurement.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="flow__grid">
          <article class="card">
            <h3>Overview & Concepts</h3>
            <p>
              Motivation, terminology, and the design-time vs runtime split in
              clear language.
            </p>
            <a href="/ed/overview/">/ed/overview/</a>
          </article>
          <article class="card">
            <h3>Core Model</h3>
            <p>
              Journeys, states, transitions, start/end, identity, and
              versioning.
            </p>
            <a href="/ed/core-model/">/ed/core-model/</a>
          </article>
          <article class="card">
            <h3>Design-Time Definitions</h3>
            <p>
              Prescriptive graphs: allowed paths, optional paths, and guards.
            </p>
            <a href="/ed/design-time/">/ed/design-time/</a>
          </article>
          <article class="card">
            <h3>Runtime Executions</h3>
            <p>
              Trace events, sessions, timing, and references to design intent.
            </p>
            <a href="/ed/runtime/">/ed/runtime/</a>
          </article>
          <article class="card">
            <h3>Metrics & Conformance</h3>
            <p>Conformance scoring, violations, drop-offs, and core metrics.</p>
            <a href="/ed/metrics/">/ed/metrics/</a>
          </article>
          <article class="card">
            <h3>Serialization</h3>
            <p>JSON / JSON-LD guidance and extensibility mechanisms.</p>
            <a href="/ed/serialization/">/ed/serialization/</a>
          </article>
        </div>
      </section>

      <section class="grid roles">
        <article class="panel">
          <h2>How to read (by role)</h2>
          <div class="role-list">
            <div>
              <h4>Product / UX</h4>
              <p>
                Overview & Concepts → Design-Time Definitions → Metrics &
                Conformance
              </p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h4>Engineering</h4>
              <p>
                Overview & Concepts → Core Model → Runtime Executions →
                Serialization
              </p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h4>Analytics / Data</h4>
              <p>
                Overview & Concepts → Runtime Executions → Metrics & Conformance
              </p>
            </div>
            <div>
              <h4>Tool builders</h4>
              <p>Core Model → Serialization → Runtime Executions</p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </article>

        <article class="panel glow">
          <h2>Publishing model</h2>
          <p>
            UJG evolves in the Editor’s Draft workspace. When parts become
            stable they are snapshotted into a new Technical Report version.
          </p>
          <ul>
            <li>Stable subset captured at a point in time.</li>
            <li>Stable URL space for implementers.</li>
            <li>ED continues iterating alongside TR releases.</li>
          </ul>
        </article>
      </section>

      <section class="cta">
        <div>
          <h2>Participate</h2>
          <p>
            UJG is developed openly. Feedback, issues, and implementation
            reports are welcome.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="cta__links">
          <a class="btn" href="/governance/">Governance</a>
          <a class="btn" href="/contributing/">Contributing</a>
          <a class="btn primary" href="https://github.com/">Issues / PRs</a>
        </div>
      </section>
    </div>
  </body>
</html>
